parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire sidewall separation can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
Spare tire hoist cable failure can cause the spare tire to fall off while driving, leading to accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Spare tire falls off while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improper tire installation or mounting can cause tire failure, leading to accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.
Failure to honor tire recalls or manufacturer warranties can lead to continued use of defective tires, increasing the risk of accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.
Other tire-related issues, such as dry rot or tire tread separation, can cause accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Timing Chain Tensioner Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain tensioner can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine makes a rattling or knocking noise
the check engine light comes on
and the engine may stall or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Fire due to Crankshaft or Camshaft Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft or camshaft can cause the engine to catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine makes a loud banging or grinding noise
and flames or smoke may be visible from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a grinding or whining noise
and may lose power or stall when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air blend door can cause the heating and cooling system to malfunction, leading to discomfort or distraction while driving.
symptoms: The heating and cooling system does not function properly
and may only blow hot or cold air.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spark plugs can cause the engine to misfire, leading to decreased performance and fuel efficiency.
symptoms: The engine makes a misfiring or sputtering noise
and the check engine light may come on.
